To run:
In BASH - "./client.c"

To Use:
There are 4 commands that the user may issue:

 - verbose -used for debugging, allows the user to see the progress being
   	   made by the program 

 - connect -used for connecting to a server. The syntax is "connect <IP:PORT>"

 - quit    -ends the program

 - send    -used to send a string to the server, which will echo the string
   	   back. The syntax is "send <string>" 
